      {
        "id": 3120413,
        "name": "Brian Buzzini",
        "username": "B_Buzzini",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/b_buzzini/{size}/636_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-03-10T21:55:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2515287&amp;iNote=9023563\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Roses de Jeanne / C\u00e9dric Bouchard Champagne Mill\u00e9sim\u00e9 Blanc de Noirs Les Ursules</strong></a> <em>- France, Champagne (3/10/2021)</em><br>\nHad along with the 12 La Boloree\u2026the first time trying the Ursules, and once again, a FANTASTIC bubbly! What strikes me in this wine is the bright laser beam energy this has, along with the fleshy ripe Pinot Noir fruit! Wasn\u2019t far off from the Boloree\u2026although that is Pinot Blanc\u2026the Ursules has intense fresh squeeze lemon/pineapple citrus\u2026salty sea air and crushed minerals\u2026wonderful ginger spiced, creamy cherry kirsch mousse that coats the palate\u2026exotic florals of white flowers, almond paste, smoky lees, red licorice\u2026SUCH harmony and pureness\u2026an absolute pleasure! So far, 2012 CB is a home run in my book! Had most of them now, give the nod to the Boloree\u2026but this and the Haute Lemble not far behind. All are 95+ <em><strong>(96 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/a/9/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/9/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"oeOOQO1xxZv2ePJGQo8GkdQ9Mq3\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/9/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/9/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/a/9/a9e1080de02993e5f6b7ca2ce73ea836ea31cf67.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"706D69\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">600\u00d7800 124 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>",
